headline: 1 Safe-and-Steady Stock with Solid Fundamentals and 2 That Underwhelm
summary: Stability is great, but low-volatility stocks may struggle to deliver market-beating returns over time as they sometimes underperform during bull markets.

headline: Assessing Henry Schein (HSIC) Valuation As Growth And Returns Face Competitive Pressure
summary: Recent commentary on Henry Schein (HSIC) has focused on its organic revenue growth falling short of benchmarks over the past two years and shrinking returns on capital, raising questions about competitive pressures and execution.
